properties.areaDesc: Rappahannock River from Urbanna to Windmill Point; York River
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 18 at 3:31PM EST until January 20 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 15 to 20 kt with gusts up to 25 kt and
waves 1 to 3 ft expected from Sunday afternoon through Sunday
night.

* WHERE...Rappahannock River from Urbanna to Windmill Point and
York River.

* WHEN...From 4 PM Sunday to 7 AM EST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM SUNDAY TO 7 AM EST MONDAY
